<TITLE> Sheikh Selim remanded for two days </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 18 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Monday sent Awami League presidium member Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim into two-day police remand in an extortion case. The Metropolitan Magistrate's Court of Selina Akhter approved the police appeal for remand when the investing officer of the case, Obaidul Haque, applied for five days to interrogate him. Azam J Chowdhury, owner of East Coast Trading Company, filed the case with Gulshan Police Station on June 13, accusing AL president Sheikh Hasina and her cousin Selim of extorting Tk 2.99 crore. Joint forces arrested Selim on May 29, before the case was filed. Selim's lawyers Sahara Khatun and Kamrul Islam mentioned his physical illness in court and the court told the investigating officer to question him with care. bdnews24.c
